docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Invoking the coronavirus crisis, the Justice Department has asked Congress to let more federal inmates serve their time at home and to steer scarce masks and testing kits to federal prisons ahead of other agencies, according to draft legislation submitted last week to congressional leaders.

headline.main: In Pandemic, Justice Dept. Seeks Video Court Hearings and Home Detention
headline.print_headline: Justice Dept. Seeks to Relax Some Rules

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — An effort by the Department of Veterans Affairs to prevent some veterans from seeking health care outside its centers drew heavy criticism from lawmakers and a vocal Fox News ally of the president, who suggested the department’s bureaucracy could undermine a signature program of President Trump’s term.

headline.main: V.A. Criticized for Effort to Keep Some Veterans Away From Private Care During Outbreak

docs.abstract: The bill moving through Congress is more than twice as large as the stimulus package passed in 2009, but it will soothe a shutdown economy for only a few months.
docs.snippet: The bill moving through Congress is more than twice as large as the stimulus package passed in 2009, but it will soothe a shutdown economy for only a few months.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — If you want to shut down an economy to fight a pandemic without driving millions of people and businesses into bankruptcy, you need the government to cut some checks. The coronavirus response deal that the Senate passed late Wednesday will get a lot of checks into the mail, but it will soothe only a few months of financial pain.

headline.main: A $2 Trillion Lifeline Will Help, but More May Be Needed
headline.print_headline: A Lifeline? At Least for a Few Months

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The British government must withhold key evidence from the United States for the trial of two Islamic State detainees because the Trump administration has not provided assurances that the men will not be executed, the British Supreme Court ruled on Wednesday.

headline.main: Citing Death Penalty, U.K. Court Blocks Giving Evidence on ISIS ‘Beatles’ to U.S.
headline.print_headline: British Court Denies Evidence to U.S.  For Trial of 2 Islamic State ‘Beatles’

docs.abstract: The largest economic stimulus measure in modern history would authorize direct payments to taxpayers and loans to small businesses, and create a $500 billion corporate bailout fund.
docs.snippet: The largest economic stimulus measure in modern history would authorize direct payments to taxpayers and loans to small businesses, and create a $500 billion corporate bailout fund.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Trump administration officials and top Democrats finalized an agreement early Wednesday morning on a roughly $2 trillion rescue package to confront the coronavirus pandemic, the largest economic stimulus measure in modern history.

headline.main: 5 Key Things in the $2 Trillion Coronavirus Stimulus Package
headline.print_headline: 5 Key Features of the $2 Trillion Rescue Package

docs.abstract: The economic stabilization package includes more than $12 billion for housing and protection from evictions and foreclosures, as the pandemic hits cities already in housing crises.
docs.snippet: The economic stabilization package includes more than $12 billion for housing and protection from evictions and foreclosures, as the pandemic hits cities already in housing crises.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Congress’s $2.2 trillion stabilization package headed for likely final passage on Friday will allocate more than $12 billion in funding for federal housing and rental assistance, a belated recognition that Americans cannot shelter in place from the coronavirus if they have no shelter.

headline.main: Congress Addresses Housing Crunch Amid Coronavirus Pandemic

docs.abstract: Congress’s emergency coronavirus bill would provide colleges and universities with about $14 billion to weather shutdowns and move to distance learning. That is unlikely to be enough.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The $2 trillion stimulus package passed by the Senate on Wednesday will send about $14 billion to colleges and universities that are hemorrhaging money as they close their campuses and try to stay afloat with distance learning.

headline.main: Colleges Get Billions in Coronavirus Relief, but Say Deal Falls Short of Needs

docs.abstract: The plan would provide direct payments to taxpayers, jobless benefits and a $500 billion fund to assist distressed businesses, with oversight requirements demanded by Democrats.
docs.snippet: The plan would provide direct payments to taxpayers, jobless benefits and a $500 billion fund to assist distressed businesses, with oversight requirements demanded by Democrats.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The $2 trillion economic stabilization package agreed to by Congress and the Trump administration early Wednesday morning is the largest of its kind in modern American history, intended to respond to the coronavirus pandemic and provide direct payments and jobless benefits for individuals, money for states and a huge bailout fund for businesses.

headline.main: Senate Approves $2 Trillion Stimulus After Bipartisan Deal
headline.print_headline: Senate Approves a $2 Trillion Virus Response

docs.abstract: Officials have teamed up with medical supply companies to speed the arrival of masks, gloves, gowns and other goods.
docs.snippet: Officials have teamed up with medical supply companies to speed the arrival of masks, gloves, gowns and other goods.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A commercial aircraft carrying 80 tons of gloves, masks, gowns and other medical supplies from Shanghai touched down in New York on Sunday, the first of 22 scheduled flights that White House officials say will funnel much-needed goods to the United States by early April as it battles the world’s largest coronavirus outbreak.

headline.main: White House Airlifts Medical Supplies From China in Coronavirus Fight
headline.print_headline: First of 22 Airlifts of Medical Supplies From China Lands in New York
